TITLE: Adding Self Return Type from Fluent Interfaces in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This rule adds 'self' return type to methods that return $this for fluent interfaces. It improves type safety and IDE support for method chaining patterns.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_311

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
final class SomeClass
{
-    public function run()
+    public function run(): self
    {
        return $this;
    }
}
```

