TITLE: Using Strict Comparison Operators for Same-Type Comparisons in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Replaces loose equality operators (== and !=) with strict equality operators (=== and !==) when comparing values of the same type, preventing unexpected type juggling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_57

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
 class SomeClass
 {
     public function run(int $firstValue, int $secondValue)
     {
-         $isSame = $firstValue == $secondValue;
-         $isDiffernt = $firstValue != $secondValue;
+         $isSame = $firstValue === $secondValue;
+         $isDiffernt = $firstValue !== $secondValue;
     }
 }
```

