TITLE: Adding Numeric Return Types Based on Strict Returns in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This rule adds int/float return types to methods based on their strictly typed return statements. It helps improve type safety by explicitly declaring numeric return types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_299

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
class SomeClass
{
-    public function increase($value)
+    public function increase($value): int
    {
        return ++$value;
    }
}
```

