TITLE: Converting isset Condition to Null Coalescing Operator (PHP 7.0)
DESCRIPTION: Replaces if statements with isset checks followed by conditional returns with the null coalescing operator (??) for cleaner and more concise code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_153

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class SomeClass
{
    private $items = [];

    public function resolve($key)
    {
-        if (isset($this->items[$key])) {
-            return $this->items[$key];
-        }
-
-        return 'fallback value';
+        return $this->items[$key] ?? 'fallback value';
    }
}
```

