TITLE: Converting switch statements to match expressions in PHP 8.0
DESCRIPTION: Replaces switch statements with the new match expression introduced in PHP 8.0, resulting in more concise and expressive code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_212

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
-switch ($input) {
-    case Lexer::T_SELECT:
-        $statement = 'select';
-        break;
-    case Lexer::T_UPDATE:
-        $statement = 'update';
-        break;
-    default:
-        $statement = 'error';
-}
+$statement = match ($input) {
+    Lexer::T_SELECT => 'select',
+    Lexer::T_UPDATE => 'update',
+    default => 'error',
+};
```

