TITLE: Adding Parameter Types Based on Method Call Types in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This rule adds parameter type declarations based on how the parameters are used in method calls. It helps maintain type consistency between method calls and their corresponding parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_301

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
class SomeTypedService
{
    public function run(string $name)
    {
    }
}

final class UseDependency
{
    public function __construct(
        private SomeTypedService $someTypedService
    ) {
    }

-    public function go($value)
+    public function go(string $value)
    {
        $this->someTypedService->run($value);
    }
}
```

