TITLE: Converting Closures to Arrow Functions in PHP 7.4
DESCRIPTION: Transforms simple closures to the new arrow function syntax introduced in PHP 7.4, resulting in more concise code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_198

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
 class SomeClass
 {
     public function run($meetups)
     {
-        return array_filter($meetups, function (Meetup $meetup) {
-            return is_object($meetup);
-        });
+        return array_filter($meetups, fn(Meetup $meetup) => is_object($meetup));
     }
 }
```

