TITLE: Removing Dead Code Statements in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This rule removes statements that have no effect on the program execution, like expressions with no assignment or side effects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_100

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
-$value = 5;
-$value;
+$value = 5;
```

