TITLE: Using First-Class Callable Syntax in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Upgrades string callback functions to first-class callable syntax using PHP 8.1 features, resulting in more type-safe and IDE-friendly code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_67

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
 final class SomeClass
 {
     public function run(array $data)
     {
-        return array_map('trim', $data);
+        return array_map(trim(...), $data);
     }
 }
```

