TITLE: Adding String Parameter Type Based on Concatenation in PHP
DESCRIPTION: The StrictStringParamConcatRector adds a string type to parameters that are used in string concatenation operations. It identifies when a parameter is concatenated with other strings and adds a string type hint.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_321

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
```diff
 class SomeClass
 {
-    public function resolve($item)
+    public function resolve(string $item)
     {
         return $item . ' world';
     }
 }
```
```

