TITLE: Simplifying Boolean Return Statements in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This rule simplifies if statements that return true or false based on a condition to a direct return of the condition.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_39

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
-if (strpos($docToken->getContent(), "\n") === false) {
-    return true;
-}
-
-return false;
+return strpos($docToken->getContent(), "\n") === false;
```

