TITLE: Adding strict_types Declaration to PHP Files
DESCRIPTION: This configurable rule adds 'declare(strict_types=1);' to PHP files. It's designed to be applied gradually to help teams transition to strict typing in their codebase.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_297

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
+declare(strict_types=1);
+
 function someFunction()
{
}
```

