TITLE: Replacing Parent Method Calls with Property Method Calls (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: ReplaceParentCallByPropertyCallRector changes method calls on parameters to calls on class properties. This is useful when injecting dependencies as properties instead of passing them as parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_266

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
final class SomeClass
{
    public function run(SomeTypeToReplace $someTypeToReplace)
    {
-        $someTypeToReplace->someMethodCall();
+        $this->someProperty->someMethodCall();
    }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Removing Redundant Try-Catch Blocks in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This rule removes try-catch blocks where the catch simply rethrows the caught exception without any additional logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_101

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
 class SomeClass
 {
     public function run()
     {
-        try {
-            // some code
-        }
-        catch (Throwable $throwable) {
-            throw $throwable;
-        }
     }
 }
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Converting isset Checks in Ternary to Null Coalescing Operator (PHP 7.0)
DESCRIPTION: Simplifies isset checks in ternary expressions to use the null coalescing operator (??) for more maintainable and readable code in PHP 7.0+.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_164

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
-isset($value) ? $value : 10;
+$value ?? 10;
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Converting func_get_args() to Variadic Parameters in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Modernizes PHP functions by replacing func_get_args() with variadic parameters (...$args), improving code clarity and parameter handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_66

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
-function run()
+function run(...$args)
 {
-    $args = \func_get_args();
 }
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Converting list() to Array Destructuring Syntax (PHP 7.1)
DESCRIPTION: Updates list() calls to use the short array destructuring syntax ([]) introduced in PHP 7.1, which is more concise and readable.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_171

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class SomeClass
{
    public function run()
    {
-        list($id1, $name1) = $data;
+        [$id1, $name1] = $data;

-        foreach ($data as list($id, $name)) {
+        foreach ($data as [$id, $name]) {
        }
    }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Adding MockObject Return Types in PHPUnit Tests
DESCRIPTION: This rule adds PHPUnit MockObject return types to methods that create and return mock objects. It improves type safety and IDE autocompletion in test classes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_306

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
class SomeTest extends TestCase
{
-    public function createSomeMock()
+    public function createSomeMock(): \PHPUnit\Framework\MockObject\MockObject
    {
        $someMock = $this->createMock(SomeClass::class);
        return $someMock;
    }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Replacing array_merge() with Spread Operator in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Modernizes code by converting array_merge() calls to use the spread operator (...), improving readability and reducing verbosity, especially when working with iterables.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/docs/rector_rules_overview.md#2025-04-16_snippet_58

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
 class SomeClass
 {
     public function run($iter1, $iter2)
     {
-        $values = array_merge(iterator_to_array($iter1), iterator_to_array($iter2));
+        $values = [...$iter1, ...$iter2];

         // Or to generalize to all iterables
-        $anotherValues = array_merge(
-            is_array($iter1) ? $iter1 : iterator_to_array($iter1),
-            is_array($iter2) ? $iter2 : iterator_to_array($iter2)
-        );
+        $anotherValues = [...$iter1, ...$iter2];
     }
 }
```

----------------------------------------

