TITLE: Creating an Async HTTP Server with ReactPHP Loop
DESCRIPTION: A basic asynchronous HTTP server implementation using ReactPHP's event loop. It sets up a TCP server on port 8080, handles incoming connections asynchronously, and includes a periodic timer to monitor memory usage.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/vendor/react/event-loop/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

use React\EventLoop\Loop;

require __DIR__ . '/vendor/autoload.php';

$server = stream_socket_server('tcp://127.0.0.1:8080');
stream_set_blocking($server, false);

Loop::addReadStream($server, function ($server) {
    $conn = stream_socket_accept($server);
    $data = "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nContent-Length: 3\r\n\r\nHi\n";
    Loop::addWriteStream($conn, function ($conn) use (&$data) {
        $written = fwrite($conn, $data);
        if ($written === strlen($data)) {
            fclose($conn);
            Loop::removeWriteStream($conn);
        } else {
            $data = substr($data, $written);
        }
    });
});

Loop::addPeriodicTimer(5, function () {
    $memory = memory_get_usage() / 1024;
    $formatted = number_format($memory, 3).'K';
    echo "Current memory usage: {$formatted}\n";
});
```

