TITLE: Generating strict unified diffs with StrictUnifiedDiffOutputBuilder
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use StrictUnifiedDiffOutputBuilder to generate strict unified diffs compatible with patch and git apply.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/vendor/sebastian/diff/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

use SebastianBergmann\Diff\Differ;
use SebastianBergmann\Diff\Output\StrictUnifiedDiffOutputBuilder;

$builder = new StrictUnifiedDiffOutputBuilder([
    'collapseRanges'      => true, // ranges of length one are rendered with the trailing `,1`
    'commonLineThreshold' => 6,    // number of same lines before ending a new hunk and creating a new one (if needed)
    'contextLines'        => 3,    // like `diff:  -u, -U NUM, --unified[=NUM]`, for patch/git apply compatibility best to keep at least @ 3
    'fromFile'            => '',
    'fromFileDate'        => null,
    'toFile'              => '',
    'toFileDate'          => null,
]);

$differ = new Differ($builder);
print $differ->diff('foo', 'bar');
```

