TITLE: Process with File Handles for Output Capture
DESCRIPTION: Example using custom pipes with file handles instead of pipes to capture command output after execution. This approach uses temporary files to store output that can be read after the process completes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rectorphp/rector/blob/main/vendor/react/child-process/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$process = new Process('ping example.com', null, null, array(
    array('file', 'nul', 'r'),
    $stdout = tmpfile(),
    array('file', 'nul', 'w')
));
$process->start();

$process->on('exit', function ($exitcode) use ($stdout) {
    echo 'exit with ' . $exitcode . PHP_EOL;

    // rewind to start and then read full file (demo only, this is blocking).
    // reading from shared file is only safe if you have some synchronization in place
    // or after the child process has terminated.
    rewind($stdout);
    echo stream_get_contents($stdout);
    fclose($stdout);
});
```

